I am super psyched for the upcoming Amy Ray Band tour, celebrating the release of “If It All Goes South”. The full band will be playing songs from all our records. 
And I couldn’t be more excited to have Kevn Kinney opening all the shows with us, doing his acoustic set. He is a an unforgettable songwriter, and compelling and funny story teller. 
Kevn and his band Drivin N Cryin gave the Indigo’s a lot of support in our early days. He is still one of my songwriting mentors. We should have our vinyl to sell by Feb as well!!

Thanks to @rhettmiller for having me on the Wheels Off podcast.
#linkinbio

“Subway” pays homage to groundbreaking radio DJ Rita Houston (a New York City legend who passed away from cancer in 2020), intensifying the track’s unfettered feeling with a luminous string section and Brandi Carlile’s yearning background vocals. “I met Rita in the ’90s and she was so dynamic—at a time when there was so much homophobia, she rooted for artists in the queer community and ended up driving a lot of people’s careers,” says Ray. “I wrote ‘Subway’ thinking about Rita and New York City, and how liberated I always felt there as a young queer person just starting to get comfortable with myself.”

Today, on the anniversary of Rita Houston’s going home (9.28.1961 - 12.15.2020), I want to honor and celebrate her poignant and joyous life. As a maverick DJ and program director at WFUV. Rita help to shape and nurture the music community for so many of us. I met Rita in the ’90s and she was a dynamo, and at a time when there was so much homophobia, she rooted for artists in the queer community and ended up driving a lot of people’s careers. I wrote “Subway" thinking about Rita and New York City, and how liberated I always felt there as a young queer person just starting to get comfortable with myself. She loved music in the deepest and most profound way. 

“Subway” is available to stream or download on all your favorite platforms.

Hope everyone is having some joyful times during these holidays. I am out in Seattle with family and since @jefffieldermusic lives out this way, we decided it would be super fun to play some songs together and do a live stream. 
We need to be getting our groove back on, because the whole band, all 7 of us- Jim, Kerry, Dan, Adrian, Jeff, Matt and me- are hitting the road for a Southern tour in February. 
Kevn Kinney is on board to open all the shows! If you live in the Northeast, we’ll be coming your way in May. 

We hope you can join us for a stripped down musical session and some friendly conversation, while Jeff and I are taking advantage of our geographical proximity.
Live from Seattle on my Facebook page, Monday Dec 26th 1:30 pm PST! (4:30 pm ET/3:30 pm CT/2:30 pm MT)
